metadata.name: Beneath the Ocean
metadata.description:
3d Illustration.
Illustrating my peaceful imagination of life beneath the ocean surface.

Beneath those stormy seas,
Who knows what you will find? 

Maybe a spiky turtle smoking a cigar.
Beneath the ocean,
Lies mysteries.
Creatures whispering. 
Currents soothing.
Everyone chilling.

Who knows what happens when no one is looking;
Yes, beneath the murky seas,
where little plant life grows,
Untouched by rays of warm sunlight.
What more happens/exists beneath, God only knows.

What lies beneath the ocean,
I often wonder what more there is.
Beneath the water cold and blue.
Filled with God's creations old and new.
